<pre><code>for item in listOfModels:     if item[0] in perms:         perms[item[0]][item[1]] = True     else:         perms[item[0]] = {item[1]: True} </code></pre>  <p>I often use code like this. Please tell me beautiful, short, right way to do same.</p>  <p>(lib's, books, samples, etc.)</p>  <p>E.G.  i have </p>  <pre><code>[     ['animal', 'rabbit'],     ['animal', 'cow'],     ['plant', 'tree'],     ['animal', 'elephant'],     ['fruit', 'strawberry'],     ['fruit', 'apple'], ] </code></pre>  <p>and need </p>  <pre><code>{     'animal': ['rabbit', 'cow', 'elephant'],     'plant': ['tree'],     'fruit': ['strawberry', 'apple'], } </code></pre>  <p>OR</p>  <pre><code>{ 'animal': {     'rabbit': True,     'cow': True,     'elephant': True }, 'plant': {     'tree': True }, 'fruit': {     'strawberry': True,     'apple': True }, </code></pre>